content.description: Located down by the water, approach by following the fisherman trail down from the east end of the old bridge. This will be the first rock outcrop after you pass the boulder with the severely overhanging start wall (sit start boulder problems). The crag is maybe 12-18Â’ tall? There are 6-7 lines on it. Good flat ground for the base. There are often fishermen hanging out at the shore of the lake, fishing.
